  "title": "The Capital's Underworld: A Night in the Garden",
  "summary": "On Ord Mantell's pleasure world of Belleau-a-Lir, the off-duty medic Myiari escapes a bad date and stumbles upon Senator Tokoga of Dac enjoying a quiet evening at a garden cafe. They are soon joined by the Verpine Dravin, who acts as the Senator's informal bodyguard, the Twi'lek engineer Ka'una, and a loud, intrusive \"drunk\" who turns out to be an assassin. When the drunk's ruse collapses, a fire erupts beneath the table and he tries to flee, only to be tackled and bitten by the diminutive Squib Kithan. After a tense standoff in which the assassin takes Kithan hostage at knifepoint, Dravin stuns him with a blaster bolt and Myiari treats his wounds. A waiter then delivers an ominous unsigned datapad message warning the Senator that far more potent tools remain at the conspirators' disposal, implicating his political rival Bavon Nass.",
